post.description:
Creates a new report in the queue specified by the `queue_slug`. Queue cannot be
in archived state.

The `entity_type` must be the name of an entity type in your schema, e.g. `user`.

Under the `entity` key, you can specify the attributes of the entity being reported.
If the entity already exists in your Cinder instance, it will be updated.
```
"entity_type": "image",
"entity": {
    "id": "foobar",
    "image": {
        "value": "https://example.com/image.png",
        "mime_type": "image/png"
    }
}
```

The optional `context` field provides extra context around the reported entity.
This lets you upsert extra entities and relationships that will help with the review,
such as information about the author of the reported entity.
For example:
```
"context": {
    "entities": [{
        "entity_type": "user",
        "attributes": {
            "id": "barbaz",
            "name": "John Doe",
            "email": "j@doe.com"
        }
    }],
    "relationships": [{
        "relationship_type": "author_of",
        "source_id": "barbaz",
        "source_type": "user",
        "target_id": "foobar",
        "target_type": "image"
    }]
}
```

You can also track the user that created the report by providing the `reporter` field:
```
"reporter": {
    "id": "deadbeef",
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane@doe.com"
}
```
This will create a `user` entity with the provided attributes and a `reporter_of` relationship
from the reporter to the reported entity. In addition, information about the reporter will be
included in the outgoing webhook when a decision is made on the report.

In addition, you can provide a list of Classifier Scores to the report by providing the `classifier_scores` field"
```
"classifier_scores": [
    {
        "attributes": ["name"],
        "groups": {
            "my-classifier-group": {
                "hate": {"score": 0.2}
            }
        }
    },
]
```

Reports can be prioritized in the selected queue by using the optional `priority` field, as a
number between 0-99 (inclusive). Priority categories can be configured in Settings > Preferences.

By default, these are the 4 priority categories:
  - 0: Low (Default)
  - 1: Medium
  - 2: High
  - 3: Critical

Jobs will be assigned by priority first and then ordered by first in, first out (FIFO).

Upserts entities and relationships that adhere to your Cinder schema.

An entity consists of a type, a set of attributes, and an optional list of classifier scores

For example:
```
{
    "entities": [
        {
            "entity_type": "user",
            "attributes": {
                "id": "foobar",
                "name": "John Doe",
                "email": "j@doe.com"
            },
            "classifier_scores": [
                {
                    "attributes": ["name"],
                    "groups": {
                        "my-classifier-group": {
                            "hate": {"score": 0.2}
                        }
                    }
                },
            ]
        },
        {
            "entity_type": "post",
            "attributes": {
                "id": "barbaz",
                "title": "Hello world",
                "images": [{
                    "value": "https://example.com/image.png",
                    "mime_type": "image/png"
                }]
            }
        }
    ],
    "relationships": [{
        "relationship_type": "author_of",
        "source_id": "foobar",
        "source_type": "user",
        "target_id": "barbaz",
        "target_type": "post"
    }]
}
```

